Catherine Nevin was jailed for life in April 2000 for arranging to have her publican husband Tom shot dead in 1996 . 
  The 62-year-old was allowed out on day release to attend an addiction studies course in Dublin . 
  She was pictured leaving Mountjoy prison and walking to her course in the city . 
  Tom was shot dead at their pub Jack White's Inn in March 1996 . 
  She has never taken responsibility for her husband's murder . 
 